#!/usr/bin/env python
"""
This script automates the generation and publication of blog posts on a WordPress site from source code files.
It leverages the OpenAI API to enhance the text and generate descriptions while identifying programming languages based
on file extensions.

Key features include:
- Command-line argument parsing for file or directory paths.
- Reading source code files to create blog post prompts.
- Utilizing OpenAI to improve text and generate HTML formatted blog content.
- Fetching or creating tags and categories in WordPress based on detected programming languages.
- Publishing posts on WordPress with generated content, titles, and excerpts.

Environment variables required for operation:
- WORDPRESS_URL: Base URL of the WordPress site.
- WORDPRESS_USERNAME: Username for WordPress authentication.
- WORDPRESS_PASSWORD: Password for WordPress authentication.
- WORDPRESS_APPLICATION: Application name for WordPress authentication.
- AI_API_KEY: API key for OpenAI.
- AI_MODEL: Model name for OpenAI API.

The script can be executed from the command line, specifying a path to a file or directory containing source code, with
an optional input string for customizing the blog post content.
